The paper focuses on recommendation settings, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the challenges of multiple stakeholders with varying goals and interests, which falls under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a multi-method evaluation approach, which can be considered as a machine learning technique and falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
